@startuml
title Virtualization architectures and their trust boundaries

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

package "Containers (shared kernel)" {
  [App A] as ca
  [App B] as cb
  [Host kernel\n(single shared kernel)] as ck
  [Hardware] as ch
  ca --> ck
  cb --> ck
  ck --> ch
}

package "Type-2 hypervisor (hosted)" {
  [Guest OS A\nkernel + apps] as g2a
  [Guest OS B\nkernel + apps] as g2b
  [Hypervisor process] as h2
  [Host OS kernel] as ho2
  [Hardware] as hw2
  g2a --> h2
  g2b --> h2
  h2 --> ho2
  ho2 --> hw2
}

package "Type-1 hypervisor (bare metal)" {
  [Guest OS A\nkernel + apps] as g1a
  [Guest OS B\nkernel + apps] as g1b
  [Thin hypervisor\n(minimal TCB)] as h1
  [Hardware] as hw1
  g1a --> h1
  g1b --> h1
  h1 --> hw1
}

note bottom of ck
  A kernel bug can be a
  container escape: one
  compromised app reaches
  the others.
end note

note bottom of h1
  Smaller attack surface:
  only the thin hypervisor
  is shared. Used by Qubes OS.
end note
@enduml
